Reasoning: The paper deals with formalisms and algorithms for comparing and expressing properties about real-time systems, which involves logical, topological, and computational aspects. The focus on formal methods and verification suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The study of stochastic systems and the development of algorithms for checking when a formula is satisfied suggest that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The consideration of time as an important factor and the development of formalisms and algorithms for comparing the real-time behaviour of systems suggest that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
